# Studio Shell (Frozen)

Read `docs/Studio_Shell_Rules.md` before any Studio change. Also read `docs/CharID_Architecture.md`, `docs/CharID_Editor_Implementation_Spec.md`, and `docs/charid_editor_layout.html`.

## Frozen (no changes unless project owner explicitly requests)

Four-column grid: icon rail (48–56px) · sidebar (260px) · canvas (flex) · inspector (260px).

Do not change: DOM hierarchy, shell class names, grid architecture, CSS variables for shell sizing, top toolbar layout, page strip, zoom bar, measurement system.

Frozen components include `CharIDEditorShell`, `EditorIconRail`, sidebar/inspector/canvas chrome, and `charid-editor-layout.css` shell rules.

## Allowed

Implement features **inside** the shell: bubble/caption/SFX libraries, draw tools, upload library, AI Generate, Properties panel fields, crop, layers, keyboard shortcuts, tablet responsiveness without altering desktop shell structure.

Bug fixes that do not restructure layout.

## Never

Redesign shell, merge sidebar/inspector, move canvas, rename CSS architecture, replace grid or measurement system.

## Regression

Preserve working behavior. Extend components; do not replace working layouts. If shell modification seems required, stop and explain why before proceeding.

CharID is an AI Production Studio, not a generic design editor. Extend functionality; do not redesign architecture.
